status: MARC21-007: Playback speed of sound recording
Playback speed of the sound recording.

definition (en): 1.4 m. per second. Speed is calculated from the distance the playback mechanism covers on the surface of the disc per second, and not the number of revolutions of the disc.

scope note (en): For example, on half-speed mini-cassettes used in small portable recorders.
For example, on consumer and nonprofessional reel-to-reel tapes, cartridges and very unusual cassette tapes.
For example, in reel-to-reel, nonprofessional, and studio tapes.
For example, on reel-to-reel, studio tapes.
For example, on reel-to-reel, studio tapes, but is rarely used.

definition (en): Speed other than 16 rpm, 33 1/3 rpm, 45 rpm, 78 rpm, 8 rpm, 1.4 m. per second, 120 rpm, 160 rpm, 15/16 ips, 1 7/8 ips, 3 3/4 ips, 7 1/2 ips, 15 ips, 30 ips.
